HEADWORD: Alcaic
<hw>Al*ca"ic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Alca⟦ium⟧cus</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to Alc⟦ae⟧us, a
lyric poet of Mitylene, about 6000 <sc>b. c.</sc></def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of verse, so called from Alc⟦ae⟧us. One
variety consists of five feet, a spondee or iambic, an iambic, a long
syllable, and two dactyls.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
